SIMPLE: forwarder
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forwarder
<hw>For"ward*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who forwards or promotes; a promoter.</def> <rj><au>Udall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who sends forward anything;</def>
<specif>specifically</specif>, <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>one who transmits
goods; a forwarding merchant, such as a <styp><ecol><b>freight
forwarder</b></ecol></styp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bookbinding)</fld> <def>One employed in
forwarding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forwarding</ent>⟦br⟧
